FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1780398175
OL,3,CPutting a deposit on vapes would
OL,4,Creduce littering, waste companies say
OL,6,FWendy Taylor, the association's health
OL,7,Fand well-being committee chairwoman,
OL,8,Fsaid: "A year on, the volume of vapes
OL,9,Fin our bins has dropped, but industry
OL,10,Fhas moved faster than regulation ` the
OL,11,Fproducts causing fires in our bin
OL,12,Florries today are effectively the same
OL,13,Fdisposables in a different shell.
OL,15,F"Year two must focus on enforcement,
OL,16,Fproducer responsibility, and closing
OL,17,Fthis industry loophole to keep
OL,18,Frechargeable vapes out of our waste
OL,19,Fsystem, preventing further fires and
OL,20,Freducing unnecessary local resource
OL,21,Fdrain."
OL,26,@pD@GOUwD@AOU}D@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
